# Purpose: Development Docker configuration for React frontend with hot reloading
# Scope: Frontend development environment setup with live reloading and debugging capabilities
# Overview: Provides development-optimized container configuration for React frontend with
#     Vite development server, hot module replacement, and debugging tools. Includes HTMLHint
#     for real-time HTML validation and exposes development server on all interfaces for
#     external access. Optimized for development workflow with fast startup and live reloading
#     capabilities. Supports volume mounting for real-time code changes and debugging.
# Dependencies: Node.js 20 alpine, npm package manager, Vite development server, HTMLHint
# Exports: Development server container exposing port 5173 with hot reloading enabled
# Interfaces: Vite dev server, hot module replacement WebSocket, and development tool access
# Environment: Development environment with debugging tools and live reloading features
# Related: package.json scripts, Vite configuration, development workflow, and debugging setup
# Implementation: Single-stage development build optimized for fast iteration and debugging

# Development Dockerfile for React frontend
FROM node:20-alpine

# Set working directory
WORKDIR /app

# Copy package files
COPY package*.json ./

# Install dependencies
RUN npm install

# Install HTMLHint globally
RUN npm install -g htmlhint

# Copy application files
COPY . .

# Expose port
EXPOSE 5173

# Run development server
CMD ["npm", "run", "dev", "--", "--host", "0.0.0.0"]
